            <p>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><pc>॥</pc><w>kantsakarṣanne</w><pc>॥</pc></p>
            <lg type="poem">
               <lg n="1" type="strophe">
                  <l n="a"><w>arai</w><w>srukalyñe</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>cisa</w><w>nta</w><w>kca</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>mā</w><w>prāskau</w></l>
                  <l n="b"><w>pontas</w><w>srukelle</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>kā</w><w>ñiś</w><w>ṣeske</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>tañ</w><w>prāskau</w></l>
                  <l n="c"><w>s=</w><w>ārai</w><w>ñi</w><w>palsko</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>cisa</w><w>prāskau</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>pon</w><w>prekenne</w></l>
                  <l n="d"><w>twe</w><w>ṅke</w><w>kalatarñ</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-s"/><w>apiś</w><w>wärñai</w><caesura ana="frg:cs-w"/><w>nreyentane</w><pc>:</pc></l>
               </lg>
            </lg>
            <p>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><w>likkhikena</w><w>dharmacandrasya</w><w>bhikṣo</w></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>16</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krauseandthomas1964"/><citedRange>63</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>54</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>75, 392</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1952"/><citedRange>18</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>32</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>78</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>90</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>192</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault2008"/><citedRange>18</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>371</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">O death, I do not fear anything but you: all have to die, why would I alone fear you? Oh, this is my idea: I am fearing because of you at all times, for you will bring me to the hells, including the Avīci!</seg></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">O Tod, ... [wenn] ich mich vor dir fürchte allezeit, wirst du aber mich in die Höllen, bis hin zur Avīci, bringen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Oh death, ... [if] I fear you at all times, you, however, will bring me into the hells, all the way to the Avīci.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>392</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">O Tod, ..., du aber wirst mich in die Höllen, bis hin zur Avīci, bringen.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">Oh death, ... you, however, will bring me to the Hells, [all the way] down to the Avīci.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>75</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a1 #a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">O death, I do not fear anything but you: all have to die, why would I alone fear you? Oh, this is my idea: «I am fearing because of you at all times, for you will bring me to the hells, including the Avīci!» (18)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>371</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">By the writing of the monk Dharmacandra</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
